In GridSerializer.processRow:

            columnsToExport.forEach((column: Column, index: number) => {
                rowAccumulator.onColumn(column, index, node);
            });

node.data will be an array here for detail rows, so the end result of the output will be blank rows for these child rows.

This would render the detail rows:

            let nodesToProcess = [node];
            if(Array.isArray(node.data)) {
                nodesToProcess = node.data;
            }
            nodesToProcess.forEach((nodeToProcess) => {
                var rowAccumulator: RowAccumulator = gridSerializingSession.onNewBodyRow();
                columnsToExport.forEach((column: Column, index: number) => {
                    rowAccumulator.onColumn(column, index, nodeToProcess);
                });
            })


But the headers wouldnt tie up with the row data, so its a slightly bigger item than just that change

Perhaps a quick fix for users is to skip child rows with array data?
